The following, reduced from UVM tests/10resources/99compat/7453_print_config_matches, results in a compile-time error:

```
Vt_0_t__03a__03aconfig_obj__Vclpkg__0.cpp:7:6: error: infinite recursion detected [-Werror=infinite-recursion]
    7 | void Vt_0_t__03a__03aconfig_obj::__VnoInFunc_post_randomize(Vt_0__Syms* __restrict vlSymsp) {
```

```
module t;

  virtual class uvm_object;
  endclass

  class config_obj extends uvm_object;
    function void post_randomize();
      super.post_randomize();
    endfunction
  endclass

  initial $finish;

endmodule
```

Currently the pre/post_randomize functions are inserted on-demand, but the super. one isn't so it calls itself due to a bug.

I'll probably get to fixing this shortly if no one else does.

